<br>
I would recommend either Ebon Storm or Dreadstorm.<br>
<br>
Ebon storm is a roleplaying guild which does a moderate amount of raiding (not really sure how much they do or dont raid, but some of them have ok gear).<br>
<br>
Dreadstorm is a raiding guild which does a tiny amount of roleplaying. Dreadstorm has no minimum raiding requirements, just that you be a nice person who is interested in the challenge or a raid rather than the phat lewt at the end of it. Thus we tend to take on mobs a tiny bit too hard for us and die a few times to get the technique right. Mobs that we are currently working on are Rumblecrush (sp?) in UP (well get you next time rumble... next time....), Innoruuk in PoH, and are going to take our first trip to ToV this weekend.<br>
<br>
Dreadstorm isnt one of the big 3 raiding guilds. But we are probably number 4 in terms of what we can take down on the server. We pride ourselves in raiding with skill rather than numbers.<br>
<br>
Anyway have a talk to some of us online, come along to some of our raids... see if you enjoy the challenges and conversations.... and take it from there<br>
<br>
