<br>
The first guild I was in back on Tunare was raiding, but friendship-based and it's night and day different from the skill/attendance style.  The latter is like playing on a semi-pro sports team -- take your pick on sport.  It's fun in some ways, but you never really get that guild-family feeling you get from a friendship-based guild. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukaisratahl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kais Ratahl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Clockwork Tiger<br>Lord of the Rawr<br> Mod of Maulings</span><br>  Posts: 569<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/10/02 12:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=299.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some advice on the 'right' guild to join </span><hr size=1> Taldaydar has it about right (cept for the &quot;some of them have ok gear&quot; part... /bonk <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br>
