<br>
Awakened Souls/Souls Arisen is disbanded, at least they effectively are.  Eight or nine members, well ex-members now, have all applied en mass to Fire and Fury.  This now swings the momentum from Reso to FnF, as their average daily raiding force will most likely exceed Resolutions.  <br>
<br>
As far as my endorcement of Dreadstorm.  While I found DS raids very enjoyable, they are much to much &quot;pick up&quot; for my taste.  Fore the two or three weeks I asked to join them, I joined them for only a single raid.  Becasue their raiding is dependent on people showing up, one can never be sure when and if a raid will mataralize.  Should Dreadstorm cement their raid schedule into something  more concrete, I'd endorce trying them as a raiding guild, until then I'd take a wait and see attitude.  The establishment of a raid schedule, especially one that involves daytime (in North America) raiding, would allow the easy assemblage of raiders who would willing join DS (applicants or not).<br>
<br>
I'd suggest DS and NC host open raids.  While this wouldn't necessarily mean that they would attract members, they may start forming the relationships necessary to do inter guild raiding with, like the Fellowship does now.<br>
