<br>
Dreadstorm however offers an attractive environment to the less dedicated, or more casual EQ players, those who have their weekends open, and don't mind a low key environment. Were I to measure guilds attractiveness, or unattractiveness, to say how much profanity and cyborz their chat channels have, I'd not give FnF, Reso, or AS a passing grade.  Each guild has their share of potty mouths, with Dreadstorm having much less so.  <br>
<br>
So while other guilds may score high in the Raiding department, Dreadstorm has its share of attractive characteristics.  Characteristics that while not ideal for me personally, might be ideal to a larger share of available players, who are unattached with guilds.<br>
